---
description: Pravah project rules (always on)
alwaysApply: true
---
- Read CLAUDE.md before editing. It is the source of truth.
- Mission (PS1 — Parking-Induced Congestion): re-express parking violations as time lost; rank
  junctions by the pressure index; expose evening blind spots; forecast next-week pressure;
  output explained officer-deployment plans.
- GLASS BOX, EXPLAINABLE BY DEFAULT: every score decomposes into named parts; every output a
  user sees states WHY. Interpretable ML only (gradient boosting + SHAP). No neural nets.
- PLAIN LANGUAGE in the UI: no "TPI", "vehicle-hours", "knapsack", "chronic/blindness/volume",
  "budget", "coverage-normalised", "queueing" in user-facing text. Jargon lives only in docs/code.
- The data is enforcement-generated and lies by omission — use coverage-normalised features,
  never raw counts that just reinforce current patrols. Feature engineering is where we win.
- Label FACT (from data), EST (modelled), and AI (the ML model's prediction) distinctly, everywhere.
- ONLY the provided parking-violation dataset. No ASTraM event/incident data, no external/live
  sources (tiles/geocoders/APIs) — disqualification risk. Demo runs fully offline; self-host fonts.
- Do NOT build: computer vision, ASTraM event/incident analytics, festival/rally forecasting,
  deep learning, live ASTraM/CCTV.
- Validated constants live in src/pravah/constants.py — authoritative, do not re-guess.
- Execute docs/MILESTONES.md in order; keep make test + make lint green per milestone.
